# Anonymous Functions 😶

Define functions on the fly, often used for short snippets passed to algorithms.

**Syntax:** `[capture](parameters) { body }`

```cpp
vector<int> v = {1, 2, 3};
for_each(v.begin(), v.end(), [](int n) {
    cout << n * n << " ";
});
```

# Let the Compiler Decide 🤖

The `auto` keyword deduces the type from the initializer.

```cpp
auto i = 5;          // int
auto d = 3.14;       // double
auto ptr = &i;       // int*

// Very useful for complex types:
// Instead of: std::map<string, vector<int>>::iterator it = ...
auto it = myMap.begin(); 
```

